## Corner And Junction Logic

Only one real `BG1` is used. In this scene the corner has nonstandard height/top relationship:

- `BG1` bbox height to `Z=880`, matching 20mm countertop thickness to reach 900mm.
- Previous scenes often used `862 + 38`; this one uses `880 + 20`.

Learning rule: working height stays 900mm, but carcass/top split can vary by countertop material/thickness. Generator checks must use declared countertop thickness, not hardcode 862/38 everywhere.

