## Generator Implications

Future EK generation should:

1. Treat standalone fridge components as real visual/check components that can remain in the scene.
2. Verify fridge zone against the actual component bbox and surrounding panels; do not create a separate measurement object.
3. Support 20mm/30mm stone countertop workflows: base/carcass top must adjust so base height + stone thickness = target work height.
4. Preserve `50+831` and `600+50` dimension expressions as intent.
5. Allow `PD1_6` to terminate the main row on the right while cooktop stays in a separate base module.
6. Support two-band `TC1` upper/antresol rows with 50mm transition fillers.
7. Classify low `PANEL-FACADE` strips by measured height; do not assume one universal plinth strip height.

## Open Items

- Add `20mm/30mm stone countertop -> adjusted base height` as a standard/check rule after comparing with more stone worktop scenes.
- Improve extractor name encoding for Russian component/material names.
- Add automatic detection of existing standalone fridge components by definition/material/name patterns.
- Add upper-row band classifier for `TC1` lower/top compositions.